National Security Advisor Tom Donilon met with Dr. Mahmoud Gibril, the President of the Libyan Transitional National Council's Executive Bureau, to discuss the situation in Libya. Donilon expressed that the United States sees the TNC as a legitimate and credible representative of the Libyan people, while emphasizing that Qadhafi no longer has the legitimacy to rule. Donilon and Gibril also discussed ways in which the United States and the coalition can provide further support to the TNC, and Donilon commended the TNC's commitment to a democratic future for Libya.